# Global Project Principles (Cursor Credits Distribution App)

## Brief Vision
Deliver a friction-free, self-service portal for distributing Cursor credits at meet-ups & hackathons. Built with Next.js 15 (App Router) + Firebase, styled with shadcn/ui + TailwindCSS, it must feel as thoughtful as an Apple product—simple, fast, and delightful.

## Guiding Philosophy
1. **Focus** – Solve one problem brilliantly: credit redemption & tracking.  
2. **Elegance** – Small, composable pieces over monoliths.  
3. **Trust** – Data integrity & privacy are first-class concerns.  
4. **Reuse** – Shareable code & rules so any ambassador can fork & run.

## Repository Structure
```
root
 ├─ .cursor/rules/        ← design & code standards
 ├─ src/                  ← application code
 │   ├─ app/              ← Next.js route handlers & pages (app router)
 │   ├─ components/       ← UI primitives (shadcn cloned components)
 │   ├─ features/         ← domain slices (codes, attendees, auth…)
 │   ├─ lib/              ← shared utils, hooks, Firebase helpers
 ├─ public/               ← static assets
 ├─ test_files/           ← sample CSVs
 └─ README_PRD.txt        ← evolving product spec
```

## Code-Style & Best Practices
- TypeScript strict mode, eslint-config-next + @typescript-eslint + Prettier.
- 80 char soft wrap, 2-space indent.
- Limit any file to ≤500 LOC; refactor into smaller modules before exceeding.
- One top-level export per file when possible.
- Favour pure functions; side-effects isolated in dedicated modules.
- Prefer async/await; avoid `then` chains.
- **Always comment why & how, not what.**  
  - Single-line `//` for quick notes.  
  - Multi-line `/** … */` JSDoc3 for APIs, hooks, components.
- Keep historical comments that remain relevant.
- Functional React components; avoid legacy class components.
- Naming: `camelCase` vars & funcs, `PascalCase` components, UPPER_SNAKE constants.

## Workflows
- Investigate requests thoroughly—search, grep, Context7 docs before coding.
- Keep README_PRD.txt synced with reality; update when scope changes.
- PRs must pass CI (type-check, lint, tests).
- Commit messages: `<scope>: <imperative summary>`.

## Dependencies (Aug 2025)
- Next.js ^15.1.8 (`/vercel/next.js`)
- React ^19
- shadcn/ui ^0.9.0 (`/shadcn-ui/ui`)
- Firebase JS SDK ^10 (`/firebase/firebase-js-sdk`)
- TailwindCSS ^4

## Principles Recap
- Simplicity over cleverness.
- Lean, tested, documented code.
- Every feature traceable to the PRD.
